timeline.bodyText:
My comments above apply here. But here's an additional one: This test is the same as the above test.
The only variables are:

selector getter
mocked setting

As I did with the UserQuery.test.ts this is a good candidate for a parameterised test. But unlike what I did over there, you'd want to go the table approach.
Something probably like (this code I just freestyled right here - disclaimer):
const getOwnerSelector = () => /*do stuff*/;
const getDateSelector = () => /*do other stuff */;
const disableOwnerSelector = {
    ...SearchSettingsModule.defaultSearchSettings,
    searchingDisableOwnerFilter: true,
  };
const disableDateModified = {
    ...SearchSettingsModule.defaultSearchSettings,
    searchingDisableDateModifiedFilter: true,
  };
it.each([
  ['Owner Selector', getOwnerSelector, disableOwnerSelector],
  ['Date Selector', getDateSelector, disableDateSelector],
])('should be possible to disable %s', async (testName, getSelector, disableSelector) => {
  expect(getSelector()).toBeInTheDocument();
  disableSelector();
  page.unmount();
  await renderSearchPage();
  expect(getSelector()).not.toBeInTheDocument();
});

